The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Nirma wins race for Saurashtra

 Mumbai, June 29 (PTI): Nirma Chemical Works has emerged as the highest bidder for acquiring 32.2 per cent of the paid-up equity capital of Saurashtra Chemicals, a SK Birla group company, along with its debt and preference shares from Asset Reconstruction Company (India) (Arcil). 

 With this transaction framework, equity and preference shares, along with secured debt and certain working capital debt have been transferred to Nirma by Asset Reconstruction Company, the company said in a release here today.

 Nirma would be required to make an open offer under the Securities Exchange Board of India (Sebi) take over regulation in pursuant to acquisition of equity stake in Saurashtra Chemicals, the release said but did not reveal the financial consideration of the deal. According to the process put in place by Arcil, binding bids were submitted for buying the 32.2 per cent stake in Saurashtra Chemicals along with its debt and preference shares and Nirma was declared as the best expressor, it said.

 With the acquisition of non-performing assets by Arcil, a part of the loan in the SK Birla company from some of the major lenders could be closed, it added. 




